This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel meta learning method to solve few-shot learning problems. It also involves training a meta model to optimize its generalizability across heterogeneous tasks, which is a common research topic in the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as few-shot learning is a popular research area in both fields. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training a hierarchical model and optimizing its performance through neural networks.
